The federal government obligated Brekford Corp. a high of $1.16 million USD in FY2014 and low of $20,000 USD in FY2007. On average, it received $265,270 United States dollars in contract obligations per fiscal year.* Dollars Obligated: The amount of money obligated towards a vendor by a federal agency or agencies to work on a contract.* Base and All Options (Ceiling): The maximum amount that can be awarded to a contract as mutually agreed upon by the vendor and agency.





