Brekford Corp. Awarded $4 Million Rugged IT Products And Services






GlobeNewswire



Mar 10, 2011 9:00 AM EST













 
















































    HANOVER, Md., March 10, 2011 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Brekford Corp. (the "Company") (OTCQB:BFDI)   www.brekford.com , a homeland security technology service provider of fully integrated vehicle upfitting services, rugged information technology and automated traffic photo enforcement solutions has announced that the Company has been awarded a quasi-government utility contract valued at up to $4M over the period of one year.  The quasi-government utility contract is of indefinite delivery and indefinite quantity. It represents blanket purchase agreement (BPA) contracts from various quasi-government utility companies. The indefinite delivery/indefinite quantity contract is valued up to $4 million over this year. Under the terms of the contracts, Brekford will supply rugged IT Panasonic Toughbook, communications and mobile computer vehicle mounting equipment.  "We have a strong history of providing unparallel services for state and local, and federal agencies. We are proud to build on this experience and sound relationships with this our newest, quasi-government utility contract award," stated C.B. Brechin, Chief Executive Officer of Brekford.   "Brekford has been awarded automatic traffic enforcement contracts by several municipalities during the past several months. The implementation of these contracts is anticipated to bring fresh revenues and profitability to the Company this quarter. Our increased revenue from the company's other suite of products serves as a significant enhancement to our broadening revenue streams," noted C.B. Brechin. "These recent awards are a strong reflection of our company's ability to execute upon the newest technology that municipalities and law enforcement require today. Our Company is hitting on all cylinders."  About BREKFORD  Brekford Corp. is a homeland security technology service provider of fully integrated vehicle upfitting and installation services, rugged computer and video technology and automated traffic safety solutions geared towards mission critical operations. For more than a decade we have provided services to branches of the U.S. military, various federal entities and numerous security and public safety agencies throughout the United States. We provide these agencies with an end-to-end suite of mobile communications, information technology, vehicle upfitting services, and automated traffic photo enforcement solutions that are designed to streamline procurement processes and offer maximum functionality to their day-to-day operations. Brekford delivers a one-stop shop. Brekford 'does it all' from Automatic Traffic Safety Solutions to providing cutting edge technology to vehicle upfitting and installation services. Additional information about Brekford may be found online at   http://www.brekford.com  The Brekford Corp. logo is available at   http://www.globenewswire.com/newsroom/prs/?pkgid=6847    Forward-Looking Statements   This press release contains forward-looking statements within the meaning of that term in Section 21E of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended. Actual results may differ materially from the results suggested by these forward-looking statements, for a number of reasons, including, but not limited to, market conditions, the cost and success of development activities and ability to successfully manage growth. Readers are referred to the documents filed by Brekford Corp. with the SEC, specifically the Company's most recent reports filed on Form 10-K and Forms 10-Q, which further identify the important risks, trends and uncertainties which could cause actual results to differ materially from the forward-looking statements in this press release. The Company expressly disclaims any obligation to update any forward-looking statements. CONTACT: COMPANY CONTACT:         C.B. Brechin, CEO         443-557-0200         investors@brekford.com                  IR CONTACT:         John Pentony         IR Affiliates         469-252-3030         john@iraffiliates.com       



 



 































































 











